
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes/relationships

class Cinema {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - town: String
}

class Theatre {
  - id: int
  - name: String
  - capacity: int
  - cinema: Cinema
}

class Movie {
  - id: int
  - title: String
  - duration: int
  - releaseDate: Date
}

class Copy {
  - id: int
  - movie: Movie
  - cinema: Cinema
}

class Show {
  - id: int
  - startTime: DateTime
  - endTime: DateTime
  - theatre: Theatre
  - copy: Copy
  - isPublished: boolean
  - isCancelled: boolean
}

class Reservation {
  - id: int
  - customerName: String
  - creditCardNumber: String
  - reservationTime: DateTime
  - show: Show
  - seats: List<Seat>
  - isCancelled: boolean
  - offerMade: boolean
}

class Ticket {
  - id: int
  - show: Show
  - seat: Seat
  - purchaseTime: DateTime
  - isAnonymized: boolean
}

class Seat {
  - id: int
  - row: int
  - number: int
  - theatre: Theatre
}

class Offer {
  - id: int
  - newShow: Show
  - newSeat: Seat
  - expirationTime: DateTime
  - accepted: boolean
  - reservation: Reservation
}

class FreeTicket {
  - id: int
  - reservation: Reservation
  - sentDate: DateTime
}

' Relationships

Cinema "1" *-- "many" Theatre : contains
Cinema "1" *-- "many" Copy : owns
Copy "1" -- "1" Movie : contains
Copy "1" -- "0..*" Show : used in
Theatre "1" *-- "many" Show : hosts
Theatre "1" *-- "many" Seat : has
Show "1" *-- "many" Reservation : has
Show "1" *-- "many" Ticket : has
Reservation "1" *-- "many" Seat : reserves
Reservation "1" -- "1" Offer : offers alternative
Offer "1" -- "1" Reservation : relates to
Reservation "1" -- "1" FreeTicket : results in
Ticket "1" -- "1" Seat : occupies

' Additional notes (optional)
note right of Reservation
  Reservations can be cancelled up to 24h before show.
  Credit card debited after cancellation period.
end note

note right of Show
  Published every Sunday for next week.
  Can be cancelled if no reservations exist.
end note

note right of Ticket
  Issued at entrance, anonymous.
  Cannot be cancelled or refunded.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Cinema**: Owns theatres and copies of movies.
- **Theatre**: Has seats and shows.
- **Movie**: Represents a film with title and duration.
- **Copy**: A physical or digital copy of a movie located in a specific cinema.
- **Show**: A scheduled screening of a movie in a theatre using a specific copy.
- **Reservation**: Customer booking of one or more seats for a show online.
- **Ticket**: A physical ticket issued either online or at the door.
- **Seat**: Identified by row and number within a theatre.
- **Offer**: Alternative seat/show offer when a show is canceled.
- **FreeTicket**: Sent home when no alternatives are available after cancellation.

